# Production target list. Read by Astro/Vite, PostCSS, and lightningcss/esbuild
# at build time. Anything supported by every browser in this set is shipped as
# modern CSS; anything not supported gets a fallback from postcss-preset-env.
#
# postcss-preset-env also disables the `custom-properties` polyfill (see
# postcss.config.mjs): our targets all support `var()`; that plugin only emitted
# legacy duplicate declarations (`prop: resolved; prop: var(--token)`).
#
# Keep the list small — every extra browser here can re-introduce verbose
# fallback CSS that the rest of the project does not need.

